udit writer | `peek/src/server/audit/writer.ts` | FR-11 writes `peek.*` to `operator_events` |\n39\t| Audit redact | `peek/src/server/audit/redact.ts` | FR-11 secret redaction |\n40\t| Mutations | `peek/src/server/mutations/README.md` (placeholder only) | FR-14 not implemented |\n41\t\n42\t### Query functions (`peek/src/server/db/queries`)\n43\t\n44\t| Query | Backs |\n45\t|-------|-------|\n46\t| `count-peek-users.ts` | `/` users table count |\n47\t| `list-peek-users.ts` | `/` users table |\n48\t| `get-peek-summary.ts` | `/` summary strip |\n49\t| `get-peek-user-detail.ts` | `/users/[userId]` (FR-6) |\n50\t| `get-command-center-attention.ts` | `/` attention queue (FR-3, FR-10 metric counts) |\n51\t| `get-recent-operator-events.ts` | `/` activity list |\n52\t| `universal-search.ts` | `/` global search (FR-5) |\n53\t| `get-growth-referrals.ts` | `/growth/referrals`, `/growth/kol` (FR-7) |\n54\t| `get-games-overview.ts` | `/games` (FR-8) |\n55\t| `get-game-rounds.ts` | `/games/[game]` (FR-8) |\n56\t| `get-round-detail.ts` | `/games/[game]/rounds/[roundId]` (FR-8) |\n57\t| `get-rewards.ts` | `/economy/rewards` (FR-9 reward economy slice) |\n58\t\n59\t### Components (`peek/src/components`)\n60\t\n61\t| Component | File | Purpose |\n62\t|-----------|------|---------|\n63\t| `AdminShell` | `admin-shell.tsx` | FR-3 persistent shell |\n64\t| `MetricStrip` | `metric-strip.tsx` | FR-4 metric primitive |\n65\t| `FilterBar` | `filter-bar.tsx` | FR-4 URL-addressable filters |\n66\t| `PeekTable` | `peek-table.tsx` | FR-13 dense sortable table |\n67\t| `StatusChip` | `status-chip.tsx` | FR-3 state primitive |\n68\t| `EmptyState` | `empty-state.tsx` | FR-3 operator empty copy |\n69\t| `DetailPanel` | `detail-panel.tsx` | FR-3 anchored sections |\n70\t| `SummaryStrip` | `summary-strip.tsx` | 303-era summary |\n71\t| `UsersTable` | `users-table.tsx` | `/` users |\n72\t| `UniversalSearchResults` | `universal-search-results.tsx` | FR-5 |\n73\t| `UserDetailView` | `user-detail-view.tsx` | FR-6 |\n74\t| `RecentActivityList` | `recent-activity-list.tsx` | `/` activity |\n75\t| `GamesOverviewTable` | `games-overview-table.tsx` | FR-8 overview |\n76\t| `GameRoundsTable`, `GameRoundsFilterBar` | `game-rounds-table.tsx`, `game-rounds-filter-bar.tsx` | FR-8 per-game |\n77\t| `CloseCallRoundsTable` | `closecall-rounds-table.tsx` | FR-8 close call |\n78\t| `RoundDetailView` | `round-detail-view.tsx` | FR-8 round detail |\n79\t| `GrowthReferrersTable`, `GrowthKolTable`, `GrowthClaimsTable`, `GrowthClaimsFilterBar` | `growth-*` | FR-7 |\n80\t| `RewardPoolCard`, `RewardConfigTable`, `RewardPoolFundingsTable` | `reward-*` | FR-9 rewards slice |\n81\t| `PaginationControls` | `pagination-controls.tsx` | FR-13 |\n82\t\n83\t### Tests (44 vitest files, 410 tests passing per iteration 41 log)\n84\t\n85\t| Layer | File | Status |\n86\t|-------|------|--------|\n87\t| Cloudflare Access verifier | `__tests__/cloudflare-access.test.ts` | Pass |\n88\t| Cloudflare proxy | `__tests__/cloudflare-access-middleware.test.ts` | Pass |\n89\t| Access policy | `__tests__/access-policy.test.ts` | Pass |\n90\t| Admin shell nav | `__tests__/admin-shell-nav.test.ts` | Pass |\n91\t| Audit writer | `audit/__tests__/writer.test.ts` | Pass |\n92\t| Per-query | `db/queries/__tests__/*.test.ts` (12 files) | Pass |\n93\t| Per-component | `components/__tests__/*.test.tsx` (24 files) | Pass |\n94\t| Lib helpers | `lib/__tests__/*.test.ts` (3 files) | Pass |\n95\t\n96\t## Acceptance Criteria Audit\n97\t\n98\t### FR-1: Cloudflare Identity Boundary\n99\t\n100\t| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n101\t|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n102\t| 1 | Production requests without valid JWT denied before render | SATISFIED | `peek/proxy.ts:50-52` returns 403; `cloudflare-access-middleware.test.ts:11-22` |\n103\t| 2 | Valid JWT but missing/invalid email denied | PARTIAL → GAP | `proxy.ts:54-56` lets request through with no header set when `verification.email === null`; `app/layout.tsx:19-31` shows access-denied panel via `AdminShell` (no 403, but children are not rendered) — denial is rendered, not a hard 403 |\n104\t| 3 | `jose` `createRemoteJWKSet` + `jwtVerify`, custom code removed | SATISFIED | `cloudflare-access.ts:1-9, 56-72`; no custom crypto/JWKS code present |\n105\t| 4 | Normalized email attached to server-side context, not from browser | SATISFIED | `proxy.ts:17-18` strips browser-supplied header; `proxy.ts:54-56` re-sets after verification; `access-policy.ts:115-125` reads only via `headers()` |\n106\t| 5 | No second global env allowlist for base access | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts` reads only `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` for role mapping; base access is Cloudflare-only |\n107\t| 6 | Dev bypass explicit, local-only via `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL` | SATISFIED | `proxy.ts:20-28`; `cloudflare-access-middleware.test.ts:39-67` (production ignores; dev honors) |\n108\t| 7 | Tests cover missing/invalid token, missing email, normalization, propagation, dev bypass | SATISFIED | `cloudflare-access.test.ts`, `cloudflare-access-middleware.test.ts` |\n109\t\n110\t### FR-2: Local Roles And Page/Action Access\n111\t\n112\t| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n113\t|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n114\t| 1 | Access checks centralized in one server-only module | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:177-218` (route + action helpers in same module) |\n115\t| 2 | Local role policy in checked-in server-only module/config | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts` (server-only, loaded via `loadPeekRolePolicyFromEnv`); `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` JSON is the policy seam |\n116\t| 3 | Exact emails supported | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:99-102` |\n117\t| 4 | Wildcard domains `*@example.com` supported | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:51-56, 99-102` |\n118\t| 5 | Case-insensitive + whitespace-trim matching | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:48, 80-85` |\n119\t| 6 | Roles limited to `business`, `admin` | SATISFIED | `lib/access-policy.ts` defines `PeekRole = \"business\" \\| \"admin\"`; `access-policy.ts:42-43` rejects others |\n120\t| 7 | One effective role; admin precedence | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:96-112` (admin returns immediately) |\n121\t| 8 | Route prefixes with role list; sensitive routes admin-only | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:150-152` (`/audit` requires admin); `getRequiredRolesForRoute` |\n122\t| 9 | Mutation action ids with role lists | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:154-159` (kol_rate.update, fraud_flag.status.update, dogpile.cancel, reward_config.update) |\n123\t| 10 | Unknown routes default; unknown actions deny | SATISFIED | `access-policy.ts:148, 201-207` (unknown action → null → false) |\n124\t| 11 | Tests cover all role/policy paths | SATISFIED | `__tests__/access-policy.test.ts` |\n125\t\n126\t### FR-3: Admin Shell And Navigation\n127\t\n128\t| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n129\t|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n130\t| 1 | Persistent shell with nav groups (Users, Growth, Games, Economy, Operations, Audit, Access) | SATISFIED | `admin-shell.tsx:42-53`; `admin-shell-nav.ts:12-20` (all 7 groups declared) |\n131\t| 2 | Shell shows verified actor email + resolved role | SATISFIED | `admin-shell.tsx:55-66` |\n132\t| 3 | Shell hides pages actor cannot access | SATISFIED | `admin-shell-nav.ts:22-28`; `app/layout.tsx:26` |\n133\t| 4 | First screen dense: search + attention + metric strip + table access | SATISFIED | `app/page.tsx:118-249` (search, attention, summary, recent activity, users) |\n134\t| 5 | No marketing hero / decorative filler | SATISFIED | `app/page.tsx` and other pages render only operator-facing content |\n135\t| 6 | Empty states explain absence in operator terms | SATISFIED | `empty-state.tsx`; used across `users-table.tsx`, growth/games tables |\n136\t\n137\t(Implicit gap not tied to a checkbox: nav has links to `/users`, `/operations/queue`, `/audit`, `/access` whose pages do not exist — covered under FR-9, FR-10, FR-11, FR-3-shell coverage. Listed under \"Recommendations\".)\n138\t\n139\t### FR-4: Data Surfacing Standard\n140\t\n141\t| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n142\t|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n143\t| 1 | Each metric has stable id, label, value, source, window, asOf | SATISFIED | `lib/types/peek.ts` `PeekMetric`; populated in `get-command-center-attention.ts:80-94`, `get-rewards.ts`, `get-games-overview.ts`, `get-growth-referrals.ts` |\n144\t| 2 | Each metric has a short definition in UI/help | SATISFIED | `PeekMetric.definition` populated; `metric-strip.tsx` renders it |\n145\t| 3 | Each summary metric links to filtered detail | SATISFIED | `drilldownHref` populated for command-center, rewards, growth, games metrics |\n146\t| 4 | Each page states freshness (live/cached/manual/sampled) | PARTIAL | `PeekMetric.freshness` exists and is set to `\"live\"`; not surfaced as a per-page banner — only per-metric |\n147\t| 5 | Sparse data renders explicit empty states | SATISFIED | Empty state copy in tables (e.g., `growth-claims-table.tsx`, `reward-pool-fundings-table.tsx`, `users-table.tsx`) |\n148\t| 6 | Monetary values display units, retain lamports | SATISFIED | `formatLamports` in queries; raw lamport string preserved (e.g., `reward-pool-card.tsx` `title=` attr) |\n149\t| 7 | Integer formatting; no float rounding for ledger values | SATISFIED | u64 round-trips as `text` everywhere; `formatCount` uses `toLocaleString` |\n150\t| 8 | Filters URL-addressable | SATISFIED | `lib/search-params.ts`, `lib/games-search-params.ts`, `lib/growth-search-params.ts` |\n151\t| 9 | Default filters prevent unbounded queries | SATISFIED | `PEEK_GAME_ROUNDS_DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE`, `PEEK_GROWTH_*_DEFAULT_LIMIT`, `PEEK_REWARD_POOL_FUNDINGS_DEFAULT_LIMIT` |\n152\t\n153\t### FR-5: Universal Search\n154\t\n155\t| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n156\t|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n157\t| 1 | Accepts user_id, username, wallet, referral code, Telegram username, Telegram provider id, round PDA, match id, tx signature | SATISFIED | `universal-search.ts:166-374` (searchUsers, searchReferralCodes, searchLinkedAccounts, searchRounds, searchTransactions, searchQueueEvents) |\n158\t| 2 | Results grouped by entity type | SATISFIED | `universal-search.ts:436-463` |\n159\t| 3 | Each result includes disambiguating context | SATISFIED | Each result has `sublabel` + `context` |\n160\t| 4 | Server-side and bounded | SATISFIED | `clampLimit` (`PEEK_SEARCH_MAX_PER_GROUP_LIMIT`); per-group `limit` clauses |\n161\t| 5 | No backend route changes | SATISFIED | All queries direct DB reads in `peek/src/server/db/queries/` |\n162\t| 6 | Logs `peek.search` with actor, query class, counts, no secrets | SATISFIED | `universal-search.ts:376-399` (`defaultPeekSearchAudit`) + redaction in writer |\n163\t\n164\t### FR-6: Expanded User Detail\n165\t\n166\t| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n167\t|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n168\t| 1 | Profile identity from `player_profiles` (heat, profile points slot, avatar) | SATISFIED | `get-peek-user-detail.ts:108-144` |\n169\t| 2 | Linked accounts state from `linked_accounts` with Telegram metadata | SATISFIED | `get-peek-user-detail.ts:289-308` (fetchLinkedAccounts) |\n170\t| 3 | Latest Telegram link tokens from `telegram_link_tokens` | SATISFIED | `fetchRecentTelegramLinkTokens` in same file |\n171\t| 4 | Referral code, inbound referrer, outbound referees, KOL rate, earnings, rebates, claim states | SATISFIED | Same file: fetchOutboundReferees, fetchKolRate, fetchReferralEarnings, fetchRecentReferralClaims |\n172\t| 5 | Points balance, lifetime, recent grants, recent crates, challenge summary | SATISFIED | fetchPlayerPoints, fetchRecentPointGrants, fetchRecentCrateDrops, fetchChallengeSummary |\n173\t| 6 | Recent game entries + transactions across all 3 games | SATISFIED | fetchRecentGameEntries, fetchRecentTransactions |\n174\t| 7 | Attention flags (failed claim, dead queue, fraud, pending SOL crate, self/loop) | SATISFIED | `get-peek-user-detail.ts:186-192` (`computeAttention`); `user-detail-view.tsx:128-145`